A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Chapter 2 of Title 1 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to persons
2 and their rights, so as to provide that life is valued and protected from the moment of
3 conception and that each life, from that moment, is accorded the same rights and protections
4 guaranteed to all persons; to provide for definitions; to provide for statutory construction; to
5 provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
7 SECTION 1.
8 Chapter 2 of Title 1 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to persons and their
9 rights, is amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
10 "1-2-12.
11 (a) As used in this Code section, the term:
12 (1) 'Abortifacient' means a method of inhibiting the development of a human pregnancy
13 at any stage following conception.
14 (2) 'Abortion' means the use of any means to terminate the pregnancy of a woman known
15 to be pregnant with knowledge that the termination will, with reasonable likelihood,
16 cause the death of the unborn child.
