17 (3) 'Conception' means the process of combining the male sperm with the female ovum,
18 resulting in a fertilized ovum or zygote.
19 (4) 'Contraception' means a method of inhibiting the development of a human pregnancy
20 at any stage prior to conception. Contraception does not include an abortifacient.
21 (b) The State of Georgia recognizes that life is valued and protected from the moment of
22 conception and that each life, from that moment, is accorded the same rights and
23 protections guaranteed to all persons by the Constitution of the United States, the Georgia
24 Constitution, and the laws of Georgia.
25 (c) This Code section shall not be construed to create or recognize a right to abortion or
26 to prohibit the use of any means of contraception."
27 SECTION 2.
28 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
